name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_black
Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the embryo sac over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The process begins with the meiosis of the megasporocyte to form four haploid megaspores. Three of the megaspores disintegrate, and the fourth undergoes mitosis giving rise to a binucleate syncytial embryo sac. The two haploid nuclei migrate to the opposite poles of the embryo sac and then undergo two rounds of mitosis generating four haploid nuclei at each pole. One nucleus from each set of four migrates to the center of the cell. Cellularization occurs, resulting in an eight-nucleate seven-celled structure. This structure contains two synergid cells and an egg cell at the micropylar end, and three antipodal cells at the other end. A binucleate endosperm mother cell is formed at the center. The two polar nuclei fuse resulting in a mononucleate diploid endosperm mother cell. The three antipodal cells degenerate.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_black
Definition: The set of processes involved in identifying and degrading defective or aberrant mRNAs within the nucleus.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_black
Definition: Any process involved in forming the mature 3' end of a U4 snRNA molecule.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_black
term: maturation of SSU-rRNA from tricistronic rRNA transcript (SSU-rRNA, 5.8S rRNA, LSU-rRNA)
Term: maturation of SSU-rRNA from tricistronic rRNA transcript (SSU-rRNA, 5.8S rRNA, LSU-rRNA)
Definition: Any process involved in the maturation of a precursor Small SubUnit (SSU) ribosomal RNA (rRNA) molecule into a mature SSU-rRNA molecule from the pre-rRNA molecule originally produced as a tricistronic rRNA transcript that contains the Small Subunit (SSU) rRNA, 5.8S rRNA, and the Large Subunit (LSU) in that order from 5' to 3' along the primary transcript.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_black
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of the mRNA transcript body that occurs when the 3' end is not protected by a 3'-poly(A) tail; degradation proceeds in the 3' to 5' direction.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_black
Definition: Any process involved in the conversion of one or more primary RNA transcripts into one or more mature RNA molecules.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_black
Definition: Any process involved in forming the mature 3' end of a U1 snRNA molecule.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_black
Definition: Any process involved in forming the mature 3' end of a U5 snRNA molecule.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_black
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways occurring in the nucleus and resulting in the breakdown of a messenger RNA (mRNA) molecule, initiated by the enzymatic addition of a sequence of adenylyl residues (polyadenylation) at the 3' end the target mRNA.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_black
Definition: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a mitochondrion; includes mitochondrial morphogenesis and distribution, and replication of the mitochondrial genome as well as synthesis of new mitochondrial components.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_black
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways occurring in the nucleus and resulting in the breakdown of an aberrant or incorrectly modified transfer RNA (tRNA) molecule, initiated by the enzymatic addition of a sequence of adenylyl residues (polyadenylation) at the 3' end the target tRNA.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_black
Definition: The covalent alteration of one or more nucleotides within an RNA molecule to produce an RNA molecule with a sequence that differs from that coded genetically.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_black
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of rRNA, ribosomal RNA, a structural constituent of ribosomes.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_black
term: exonucleolytic trimming to generate mature 3'-end of 5.8S rRNA from tricistronic rRNA transcript (SSU-rRNA, 5.8S rRNA, LSU-rRNA)
Term: exonucleolytic trimming to generate mature 3'-end of 5.8S rRNA from tricistronic rRNA transcript (SSU-rRNA, 5.8S rRNA, LSU-rRNA)
Definition: Exonucleolytic digestion of a pre-rRNA molecule to generate the mature 3'-end of a 5.8S rRNA molecule derived from an originally tricistronic pre-rRNA transcript that contained the Small Subunit (SSU) rRNA, the 5.8S rRNA, and the Large Subunit (LSU) rRNA in that order from 5' to 3' along the primary transcript.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_black
Definition: The process in which DNA-dependent DNA replication is started; this begins with the ATP dependent loading of an initiator complex onto the DNA, this is followed by DNA melting and helicase activity. In bacteria, the gene products that enable the helicase activity are loaded after the initial melting and in archaea and eukaryotes, the gene products that enable the helicase activity are inactive when they are loaded and subsequently activate.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_black
Definition: A cellular process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of ribosome subunits; includes transport to the sites of protein synthesis.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_black
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of amino acids, organic acids containing one or more amino substituents.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_black
Definition: The process preceding formation of the peptide bond between the first two amino acids of a protein. This includes the formation of a complex of the ribosome, mRNA or circRNA, and an initiation complex that contains the first aminoacyl-tRNA.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_black
Definition: The joining of 2 or more lipid bilayer membranes that surround the nucleus.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The cellular metabolic process in which a protein is formed, using the sequence of a mature mRNA or circRNA molecule to specify the sequence of amino acids in a polypeptide chain. Translation is mediated by the ribosome, and begins with the formation of a ternary complex between aminoacylated initiator methionine tRNA, GTP, and initiation factor 2, which subsequently associates with the small subunit of the ribosome and an mRNA or circRNA. Translation ends with the release of a polypeptide chain from the ribosome.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein or peptide by hydrolysis of its peptide bonds that is mediated by the proteasome but do not involve ubiquitin.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein or peptide by hydrolysis of its peptide bonds that is mediated by the proteasome.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a cadmium (Cd) ion stimulus.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein or peptide by hydrolysis of its peptide bonds, initiated by the covalent attachment of ubiquitin, and mediated by the proteasome.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: A cellular process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of ribosome subunits; includes transport to the sites of protein synthesis.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a cytokinin stimulus.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein or peptide by hydrolysis of its peptide bonds, initiated by the covalent attachment of a ubiquitin group, or multiple ubiquitin groups, to the protein.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The directed movement of proteins in a cell, including the movement of proteins between specific compartments or structures within a cell, such as organelles of a eukaryotic cell.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a protein in the cytoplasm. This is a ribosome-mediated process in which the information in messenger RNA (mRNA) is used to specify the sequence of amino acids in the protein.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus indicating an increase or decrease in the concentration of salt (particularly but not exclusively sodium and chloride ions) in the environment.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: A cellular transport process in which transported substances are moved in membrane-bounded vesicles; transported substances are enclosed in the vesicle lumen or located in the vesicle membrane. The process begins with a step that directs a substance to the forming vesicle, and includes vesicle budding and coating. Vesicles are then targeted to, and fuse with, an acceptor membrane.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a zinc ion stimulus.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a carbohydrate into pyruvate, with the concomitant production of a small amount of ATP and the reduction of NAD(P) to NAD(P)H. Glycolysis begins with the metabolism of a carbohydrate to generate products that can enter the pathway and ends with the production of pyruvate. Pyruvate may be converted to acetyl-coenzyme A, ethanol, lactate, or other small molecules.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The directed movement of substances from the endoplasmic reticulum (ER) to the Golgi, mediated by COP II vesicles. Small COP II coated vesicles form from the ER and then fuse directly with the cis-Golgi. Larger structures are transported along microtubules to the cis-Golgi.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of constituent RNAs and proteins to form the large ribosomal subunit.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of constituent RNAs and proteins to form the small ribosomal subunit.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: Any process that results in the specification, formation or maintenance of the physical structure of eukaryotic chromatin.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a mature, active proteasome complex.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The process of assisting in the covalent and noncovalent assembly of single chain polypeptides or multisubunit complexes into the correct tertiary structure.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The joining together of exons from one or more primary transcripts of messenger RNA (mRNA) and the excision of intron sequences, via a spliceosomal mechanism, so that mRNA consisting only of the joined exons is produced.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The transport of protons across a membrane to generate an electrochemical gradient (proton-motive force) that powers ATP synthesis.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: A light-dependent catabolic process occurring concomitantly with photosynthesis in plants (especially C3 plants) whereby dioxygen (O2) is consumed and carbon dioxide (CO2) is evolved. The substrate is glycolate formed in large quantities in chloroplasts from 2-phosphoglycolate generated from ribulose 1,5-bisphosphate by the action of ribulose-bisphosphate carboxylase; the glycolate enters the peroxisomes where it is converted by glycolate oxidase to glyoxylate which undergoes transamination to glycine. This then passes into the mitochondria where it is decarboxylated forming one molecule of serine for every two molecules of glycine. This pathway also exists in photosynthetic bacteria.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: A series of molecular signals within the cell that are mediated by a member of the Rab family of proteins switching to a GTP-bound active state.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The successive addition of amino acid residues to a nascent polypeptide chain during protein biosynthesis.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The directed movement of proteins into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: Any cellular process that depends upon or alters the microtubule cytoskeleton, that part of the cytoskeleton comprising microtubules and their associated proteins.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: A protein folding process that takes place in the endoplasmic reticulum (ER). Secreted, plasma membrane and organelle proteins are folded in the ER, assisted by chaperones and foldases (protein disulphide isomerases), and additional factors required for optimal folding (ATP, Ca2+ and an oxidizing environment to allow disulfide bond formation).

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a heat stimulus, a temperature stimulus above the optimal temperature for that organism.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: Any process that maintains the redox environment of a cell or compartment within a cell.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The directed movement of substances into, out of or within a vacuole.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The formation of glucose from noncarbohydrate precursors, such as pyruvate, amino acids and glycerol.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The process of introducing a phosphate group into a nucleoside diphosphate to produce a nucleoside triphosphate.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of UTP, uridine (5'-)triphosphate.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stress acting at the endoplasmic reticulum. ER stress usually results from the accumulation of unfolded or misfolded proteins in the ER lumen.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of adenosine monophosphate (AMP) from derivatives of it (either adenine, ADP or adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate) without de novo synthesis.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising microtubules and their associated proteins.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The formation or destruction of chromatin structures.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: A process of translational elongation that takes place when a ribosome has stalled during translation, and results in freeing the ribosome from the stalled translation complex.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: Any process which produces a purine nucleoside from derivatives of it, without de novo synthesis.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: Any intracellular signal transduction in which the signal is passed on within the cell via calcium ions.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of oxidative stress, a state often resulting from exposure to high levels of reactive oxygen species, e.g. superoxide anions, hydrogen peroxide (H2O2), and hydroxyl radicals.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
term: regulation of alternative mRNA splicing, via spliceosome
Term: regulation of alternative mRNA splicing, via spliceosome
Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of alternative splicing of nuclear mRNAs.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of GTP, guanosine triphosphate.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: Any process involved in the maturation of a precursor Large SubUnit (LSU) ribosomal RNA (rRNA) molecule into a mature LSU-rRNA molecule.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The enzymatic release of energy from inorganic and organic compounds (especially carbohydrates and fats) which requires oxygen as the terminal electron acceptor.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The process of directing proteins towards the chloroplast, usually using signals contained within the protein. Imported proteins are synthesized as cytosolic precursors containing N-terminal uptake-targeting sequences that direct each protein to its correct subcompartment and are subsequently cleaved.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The progressive compaction of dispersed interphase chromatin into threadlike chromosomes prior to mitotic or meiotic nuclear division, or during apoptosis, in eukaryotic cells.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The process of removing sections of the primary RNA transcript to remove sequences not present in the mature form of the RNA and joining the remaining sections to form the mature form of the RNA.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The process in which a SUMO protein (small ubiquitin-related modifier) is conjugated to a target protein via an isopeptide bond between the carboxyl terminus of SUMO with an epsilon-amino group of a lysine residue of the target protein.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of xylan, a polymer containing a beta-1,4-linked D-xylose backbone.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of acetyl-CoA from pyruvate.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
term: embryo development ending in seed dormancy
Term: embryo development ending in seed dormancy
Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the embryo over time, from zygote formation to the end of seed dormancy. An example of this process is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: A nearly universal metabolic pathway in which the acetyl group of acetyl coenzyme A is effectively oxidized to two CO2 and four pairs of electrons are transferred to coenzymes. The acetyl group combines with oxaloacetate to form citrate, which undergoes successive transformations to isocitrate, 2-oxoglutarate, succinyl-CoA, succinate, fumarate, malate, and oxaloacetate again, thus completing the cycle. In eukaryotes the tricarboxylic acid is confined to the mitochondria. See also glyoxylate cycle.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of CTP, cytidine 5'-triphosphate.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of endosomes.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a nucleoside triphosphate, a compound consisting of a nucleobase linked to a deoxyribose or ribose sugar esterified with triphosphate on the sugar.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: A series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of an extracellular ligand to the receptor Notch on the surface of a target cell, and ending with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The transport of protons against an electrochemical gradient, using energy from electron transport.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an embryo from its formation until the end of its embryonic life stage. The end of the embryonic stage is organism-specific. For example, for mammals, the process would begin with zygote formation and end with birth. For insects, the process would begin at zygote formation and end with larval hatching. For plant zygotic embryos, this would be from zygote formation to the end of seed dormancy. For plant vegetative embryos, this would be from the initial determination of the cell or group of cells to form an embryo until the point when the embryo becomes independent of the parent plant.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of oxidative stress, a state often resulting from exposure to high levels of reactive oxygen species, e.g. superoxide anions, hydrogen peroxide (H2O2), and hydroxyl radicals.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The series of steps necessary to target endoplasmic reticulum (ER)-resident proteins for degradation by the cytoplasmic proteasome. Begins with recognition of the ER-resident protein, includes retrotranslocation (dislocation) of the protein from the ER to the cytosol, protein ubiquitination necessary for correct substrate transfer, transport of the protein to the proteasome, and ends with degradation of the protein by the cytoplasmic proteasome.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of nuclear-transcribed mRNAs in eukaryotic cells.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a vesicle.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: Reactions triggered in response to the presence of a bacterium that act to protect the cell or organism.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of proteins by the translation of mRNA in a mitochondrion.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: Any process that generates adenine, 6-aminopurine, from derivatives of it without de novo synthesis.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways involving isocitrate, the anion of isocitric acid, 1-hydroxy-1,2,3-propanetricarboxylic acid. Isocitrate is an important intermediate in the TCA cycle and the glycoxylate cycle.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The regionalization process in which differences in cell differentiation along the adaxial/abaxial are generated. Adaxial refers to being situated toward an axis of an anatomical structure. Abaxial refers to being situated away from an axis of an anatomical structure.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The modification of a protein by cis-trans isomerization of a proline residue.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
term: mitochondrial electron transport, ubiquinol to cytochrome c
Term: mitochondrial electron transport, ubiquinol to cytochrome c
Definition: The transfer of electrons from ubiquinol to cytochrome c that occurs during oxidative phosphorylation, mediated by the multisubunit enzyme known as complex III.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The process of directing proteins towards and into the mitochondrion, usually mediated by mitochondrial proteins that recognize signals contained within the imported protein.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a nucleoside, a nucleobase linked to either beta-D-ribofuranose (a ribonucleoside) or 2-deoxy-beta-D-ribofuranose, (a deoxyribonucleoside), e.g. adenosine, guanosine, inosine, cytidine, uridine and deoxyadenosine, deoxyguanosine, deoxycytidine and thymidine (= deoxythymidine).

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of DNA recombination.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The retention in the endoplasmic reticulum (ER) lumen of soluble resident proteins. Sorting receptors retrieve proteins with ER localization signals, such as KDEL and HDEL sequences or some transmembrane domains, that have escaped to the cis-Golgi network and return them to the ER. Abnormally folded proteins and unassembled subunits are also selectively retained in the ER.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
term: maturation of SSU-rRNA from tricistronic rRNA transcript (SSU-rRNA, 5.8S rRNA, LSU-rRNA)
Term: maturation of SSU-rRNA from tricistronic rRNA transcript (SSU-rRNA, 5.8S rRNA, LSU-rRNA)
Definition: Any process involved in the maturation of a precursor Small SubUnit (SSU) ribosomal RNA (rRNA) molecule into a mature SSU-rRNA molecule from the pre-rRNA molecule originally produced as a tricistronic rRNA transcript that contains the Small Subunit (SSU) rRNA, 5.8S rRNA, and the Large Subunit (LSU) in that order from 5' to 3' along the primary transcript.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
term: mitochondrial electron transport, NADH to ubiquinone
Term: mitochondrial electron transport, NADH to ubiquinone
Definition: The transfer of electrons from NADH to ubiquinone that occurs during oxidative phosphorylation, mediated by the multisubunit enzyme known as complex I.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways involving succinyl-CoA, a compound composed of the monovalent acyl group 3-carboxypropanoyl, derived from succinic acid by loss of one OH group, linked to coenzyme A.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: NA

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: Ordering of successions of nucleosomes into regular arrays so that nucleosomes are positioned at defined distances from one another.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: Any process involved in the conversion of a primary mRNA transcript into one or more mature mRNA(s) prior to translation into polypeptide.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
term: response to molecule of fungal origin
Term: response to molecule of fungal origin
Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus by molecules of fungal origin such as chito-octamer oligosaccharide.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_blue
Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving RNA.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The cellular metabolic process in which a protein is formed, using the sequence of a mature mRNA or circRNA molecule to specify the sequence of amino acids in a polypeptide chain. Translation is mediated by the ribosome, and begins with the formation of a ternary complex between aminoacylated initiator methionine tRNA, GTP, and initiation factor 2, which subsequently associates with the small subunit of the ribosome and an mRNA or circRNA. Translation ends with the release of a polypeptide chain from the ribosome.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: A cellular process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of ribosome subunits; includes transport to the sites of protein synthesis.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: Any process involved in the conversion of a primary ribosomal RNA (rRNA) transcript into one or more mature rRNA molecules.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of constituent RNAs and proteins to form the large ribosomal subunit.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: Any process involved in the conversion of a primary mRNA transcript into one or more mature mRNA(s) prior to translation into polypeptide.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a cadmium (Cd) ion stimulus.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of constituent RNAs and proteins to form the small ribosomal subunit.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The process preceding formation of the peptide bond between the first two amino acids of a protein. This includes the formation of a complex of the ribosome, mRNA or circRNA, and an initiation complex that contains the first aminoacyl-tRNA.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a protein in the cytoplasm. This is a ribosome-mediated process in which the information in messenger RNA (mRNA) is used to specify the sequence of amino acids in the protein.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The covalent alteration of one or more nucleotides within an RNA molecule to produce an RNA molecule with a sequence that differs from that coded genetically.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The process of assisting in the covalent and noncovalent assembly of single chain polypeptides or multisubunit complexes into the correct tertiary structure.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The process carried out by a cell that restores the biological activity of an unfolded or misfolded protein, using helper proteins such as chaperones.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
term: endonucleolytic cleavage to generate mature 3'-end of SSU-rRNA from (SSU-rRNA, 5.8S rRNA, LSU-rRNA)
Term: endonucleolytic cleavage to generate mature 3'-end of SSU-rRNA from (SSU-rRNA, 5.8S rRNA, LSU-rRNA)
Definition: Endonucleolytic cleavage at the 3'-end of the SSU-rRNA from an originally tricistronic rRNA transcript that contained the Small Subunit (SSU) rRNA, the 5.8S rRNA, and the Large Subunit (LSU) rRNA in that order from 5' to 3' along the primary transcript, to produce the mature end of the SSU-rRNA.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The conversion of a cytosine residue to uridine in an RNA molecule by deamination.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The modification of a histone by addition of a methyl group to an arginine residue.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of valine, 2-amino-3-methylbutanoic acid.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of isoleucine, (2R*,3R*)-2-amino-3-methylpentanoic acid.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The directed movement of rRNA from the nucleus to the cytoplasm; the rRNA is usually in the form of ribonucleoproteins.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of amino acids containing a branched carbon skeleton, comprising isoleucine, leucine and valine.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
term: regulation of alternative mRNA splicing, via spliceosome
Term: regulation of alternative mRNA splicing, via spliceosome
Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of alternative splicing of nuclear mRNAs.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
term: endonucleolytic cleavage in ITS1 to separate SSU-rRNA from 5.8S rRNA and LSU-rRNA from tricistronic rRNA transcript (SSU-rRNA, 5.8S rRNA, LSU-rRNA)
Term: endonucleolytic cleavage in ITS1 to separate SSU-rRNA from 5.8S rRNA and LSU-rRNA from tricistronic rRNA transcript (SSU-rRNA, 5.8S rRNA, LSU-rRNA)
Definition: Endonucleolytic cleavage between the SSU-rRNA and the 5.8S rRNA of an rRNA molecule originally produced as a tricistronic rRNA transcript that contained the Small SubUnit (SSU) rRNA, the 5.8S rRNA, and the Large SubUnit (LSU) rRNA, in that order, from 5' to 3' along the primary transcript.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of indole-3-acetic acid, a compound which functions as a growth regulator in plants.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of the large and small ribosomal subunits into a functional ribosome.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of UMP, uridine monophosphate, starting with the synthesis of (S)-dihydroorotate from bicarbonate; UMP biosynthesis may either occur via reduction by quinone, NAD(+) or oxygen.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The covalent alteration within the mitochondrion of one or more nucleotides within an mRNA to produce an mRNA molecule with a sequence that differs from that coded genetically.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The process of removing sections of the primary RNA transcript to remove sequences not present in the mature form of the RNA and joining the remaining sections to form the mature form of the RNA.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
term: maturation of LSU-rRNA from tricistronic rRNA transcript (SSU-rRNA, 5.8S rRNA, LSU-rRNA)
Term: maturation of LSU-rRNA from tricistronic rRNA transcript (SSU-rRNA, 5.8S rRNA, LSU-rRNA)
Definition: Any process involved in the maturation of a precursor Large SubUnit (LSU) ribosomal RNA (rRNA) molecule into a mature LSU-rRNA molecule from the pre-rRNA molecule originally produced as a tricistronic rRNA transcript that contains the Small Subunit (SSU) rRNA, 5.8S rRNA, and Large Subunit (LSU) in that order from 5' to 3' along the primary transcript.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The process of assisting in the folding of a nascent peptide chain into its correct tertiary structure.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of tryptophan, the chiral amino acid 2-amino-3-(1H-indol-3-yl)propanoic acid.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
term: maturation of SSU-rRNA from tricistronic rRNA transcript (SSU-rRNA, 5.8S rRNA, LSU-rRNA)
Term: maturation of SSU-rRNA from tricistronic rRNA transcript (SSU-rRNA, 5.8S rRNA, LSU-rRNA)
Definition: Any process involved in the maturation of a precursor Small SubUnit (SSU) ribosomal RNA (rRNA) molecule into a mature SSU-rRNA molecule from the pre-rRNA molecule originally produced as a tricistronic rRNA transcript that contains the Small Subunit (SSU) rRNA, 5.8S rRNA, and the Large Subunit (LSU) in that order from 5' to 3' along the primary transcript.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The process of directing proteins towards and into the mitochondrion, usually mediated by mitochondrial proteins that recognize signals contained within the imported protein.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of lysine, via the intermediate diaminopimelate.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a mitochondrion; includes mitochondrial morphogenesis and distribution, and replication of the mitochondrial genome as well as synthesis of new mitochondrial components.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The covalent alteration of one or more nucleotides within a tRNA molecule to produce a tRNA molecule with a sequence that differs from that coded genetically.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: NA

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of pyrimidine nucleobases, 1,3-diazine, organic nitrogenous bases, beginning with the synthesis of a pyrimidine ring from simpler precursors.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
term: embryo development ending in seed dormancy
Term: embryo development ending in seed dormancy
Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the embryo over time, from zygote formation to the end of seed dormancy. An example of this process is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of arginine, 2-amino-5-(carbamimidamido)pentanoic acid.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: Any process that increases freezing tolerance of an organism in response to low, nonfreezing temperatures.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a pyrimidine ribonucleotide, a compound consisting of nucleoside (a pyrimidine base linked to a ribose sugar) esterified with a phosphate group at either the 3' or 5'-hydroxyl group of the sugar.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The directed movement of mRNA, messenger ribonucleic acid, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The creation of a single nucleus from multiple nuclei as a result of fusing the lipid bilayers that surround each nuclei.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of IMP, inosine monophosphate, by the stepwise assembly of a purine ring on ribose 5-phosphate.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The process in which a pre-tRNA molecule is converted to a mature tRNA, ready for addition of an aminoacyl group.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a cytokinin stimulus.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
term: protein import into mitochondrial inner membrane
Term: protein import into mitochondrial inner membrane
Definition: The process comprising the import of proteins into the mitochondrion from outside the organelle and their insertion into the mitochondrial inner membrane. The translocase of the outer membrane complex mediates the passage of these proteins across the outer membrane, after which they are guided by either of two inner membrane translocase complexes into their final destination in the inner membrane.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus from an insect.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The successive addition of amino acid residues to a nascent polypeptide chain during protein biosynthesis.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The joining together, after removal of an intervening sequence composed of one or more introns, of two segments of the same RNA molecule via spliceosomal catalysis to produce an mRNA composed only of exon sequences that all came from the same primary transcript.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a purine ribonucleotide, a compound consisting of ribonucleoside (a purine base linked to a ribose sugar) esterified with a phosphate group at either the 3' or 5'-hydroxyl group of the sugar.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The process of assisting in the correct posttranslational noncovalent assembly of proteins, which is dependent on additional protein cofactors. This process occurs over one or several cycles of nucleotide hydrolysis-dependent binding and release.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of tryptophan, the chiral amino acid 2-amino-3-(1H-indol-3-yl)propanoic acid; tryptophan is synthesized from chorismate via anthranilate.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: The posttranscriptional addition of methyl groups to specific residues in a tRNA molecule.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
Definition: Posttranscriptional addition of a methyl group to either a nucleotide or 2'-O ribose in a polyribonucleotide. Usually uses S-adenosylmethionine as a cofactor.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_brown
term: mitochondrial double-strand break repair via homologous recombination
Term: mitochondrial double-strand break repair via homologous recombination
Definition: The repair of a double-strand break in mitochondrial DNA in which the broken DNA molecule is repaired using homologous sequences.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of glucosinolates, substituted thioglucosides found in rapeseed products and related cruciferae.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
term: transmembrane receptor protein tyrosine kinase signaling pathway
Term: transmembrane receptor protein tyrosine kinase signaling pathway
Definition: A series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of an extracellular ligand to a receptor on the surface of the target cell where the receptor possesses tyrosine kinase activity, and ending with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: The cellular synthesis of messenger RNA (mRNA) from a DNA template.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: The formation of a syncytium, a mass of cytoplasm containing several nuclei enclosed within a single plasma membrane. Syncytia are normally derived from single cells that fuse or fail to complete cell division.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a cyclopentenone stimulus. Cyclopentenones are oxylipins derived from polyunsaturated fatty acids. They are structurally similar to jasmonic acid, but contain a reactive unsaturated carbonyl structure in the cyclo-ring. Cyclopentenones include phytoprostanes and 12-oxo-phytodienoic acid.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cellular DNA-templated transcription.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: A series of molecular signals generated by the binding of the plant hormone auxin to a receptor, and ending with modulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of hydrogen sulfide, H2S.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: The series of events causing chemical and structural alterations of an existing cellulose and pectin-containing cell wall that results in greater extensibility of the wall. An example of this is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: A process that results in the assembly and arrangement of constituent parts of the cellulose and pectin-containing cell wall, or in the disassembly of the cellulose and pectin-containing cell wall. This process is carried out at the cellular level. An example of this process is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: The formation of the primary meristem or meristematic tissue that gives rise to the primary vascular tissue.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: A homeostatic process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of a carbohydrate within an organism or cell.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of leucine, 2-amino-4-methylpentanoic acid.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: The process, occurring after plant embryonic development, by which anatomical structures are generated and organized.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
term: positive regulation of auxin metabolic process
Term: positive regulation of auxin metabolic process
Definition: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving auxins, plant hormones that regulate aspects of plant growth.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
term: positive regulation of tryptophan metabolic process
Term: positive regulation of tryptophan metabolic process
Definition: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving tryptophan, the chiral amino acid 2-amino-3-(1H-indol-3-yl)propanoic acid.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: The directed movement of substances, into, out of or within the phloem during long distance transport between source and sink tissues.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: The pathways by which inorganic sulfate is processed and incorporated into sulfated compounds.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: Any process that stops or reduces the activity of an enzyme.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: Any process that increases the rate or frequency of phosphatase activity. Phosphatases catalyze the hydrolysis of phosphoric monoesters, releasing inorganic phosphate.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or decreases the rate of addition of phosphate groups to a molecule.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of pectin, a polymer containing a backbone of alpha-1,4-linked D-galacturonic acid residues.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: The process that determines the orientation of petals with reference to the central axis.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the perianth over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The perianth is a collective phyllome structure composed of two or more petals, sepals, or tepals.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: Generation of the male gamete; specialised haploid cells produced by meiosis and along with a female gamete takes part in sexual reproduction.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of growth of an organ of an organism.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of cytokinins, a class of adenine-derived compounds that can function in plants as growth regulators.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of glucosinolates, substituted thioglucosides found in rapeseed products and related cruciferae.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: The process of introducing a phosphate group on to a protein.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a protein. Includes protein modification.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus from a nematode.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: The formation of the principal food-conducting tissue of a vascular plant.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an auxin stimulus.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: A process that results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the cell wall, the rigid or semi-rigid envelope lying outside the cell membrane of plant, fungal and most prokaryotic cells, maintaining their shape and protecting them from osmotic lysis.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: The formation of the principal water-conducting tissue of a vascular plant.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the petal over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: The process in which a cell irreversibly increases in size in one [spatial] dimension or along one axis, resulting in the morphogenesis of the cell.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: The process in which relatively unspecialized cells, e.g. embryonic or regenerative cells, acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize the cells, tissues, or organs of the mature organism or some other relatively stable phase of the organism's life history. Differentiation includes the processes involved in commitment of a cell to a specific fate and its subsequent development to the mature state.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: A conserved series of molecular signals found in prokaryotes and eukaryotes; involves autophosphorylation of a histidine kinase and the transfer of the phosphate group to an aspartate that then acts as a phospho-donor to response regulator proteins.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cellular DNA-templated transcription.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_cyan
Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of root development.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a junction between cells.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: A process that results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the cell wall, the rigid or semi-rigid envelope lying outside the cell membrane of plant, fungal and most prokaryotic cells, maintaining their shape and protecting them from osmotic lysis.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: A cellular process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of a cell wall. Includes biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, such as proteins and polysaccharides, and those macromolecular modifications that are involved in synthesis or assembly of the cellular component. A cell wall is the rigid or semi-rigid envelope lying outside the cell membrane of plant, fungal and most prokaryotic cells, maintaining their shape and protecting them from osmotic lysis.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: The directed movement of water (H2O) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of a trichoblast, a root epidermal cell that will give rise to a root hair.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a root hair cell over time, from its formation to the mature state.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways involving xyloglucan, the cross-linking glycan composed of (1->4)-beta-D-glucan backbone substituted at regular intervals with beta-D-xylosyl-(1->6) residues, which is present in the primary cell wall of most higher plants.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: The process in which the root hair grows longer.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: The series of events leading to chemical and structural alterations of an existing cell wall that can result in loosening, increased extensibility or disassembly.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of hydrogen peroxide (H2O2).

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: The change in form (cell shape and size) that occurs when relatively unspecialized cells, e.g. embryonic or regenerative cells, acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize the cells, tissues, or organs of the mature organism or some other relatively stable phase of the organism's life history.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: Localized growth of a plant root hair tip by extension of the cell wall.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell in the root epidermis acquires the specialized features of a trichoblast or atrichoblast.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: A process that results in the assembly and arrangement of constituent parts of the cellulose and pectin-containing cell wall, or in the disassembly of the cellulose and pectin-containing cell wall. This process is carried out at the cellular level. An example of this process is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: The process in which hydrogen peroxide is transported across a membrane.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
term: cellular response to calcium ion starvation
Term: cellular response to calcium ion starvation
Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of deprivation of calcium ions.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: The process in which a cell irreversibly increases in size in one [spatial] dimension or along one axis, resulting in the morphogenesis of the cell.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: The cellular chemical reactions and pathways involving nucleotide-sugars, any nucleotide-carbohydrate in which the distal phosphoric residue of a nucleoside 5'-diphosphate is in glycosidic linkage with a monosaccharide or monosaccharide derivative.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways involving GDP-mannose, a substance composed of mannose in glycosidic linkage with guanosine diphosphate.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: The directed movement of urea into, out of or within the cell. Urea is the water-soluble compound H2N-CO-NH2.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a root hair cell.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: The evagination of a membrane, resulting in formation of a vesicle.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: Growth that occurs specifically at the tip of a cell.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgreen
Definition: The process that results in the assembly of clathrin triskelia into the ordered structure known as a clathrin cage.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgrey
Definition: The cellular metabolic process in which a protein is formed, using the sequence of a mature mRNA or circRNA molecule to specify the sequence of amino acids in a polypeptide chain. Translation is mediated by the ribosome, and begins with the formation of a ternary complex between aminoacylated initiator methionine tRNA, GTP, and initiation factor 2, which subsequently associates with the small subunit of the ribosome and an mRNA or circRNA. Translation ends with the release of a polypeptide chain from the ribosome.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgrey
Definition: Any process involved in the conversion of a primary ribosomal RNA (rRNA) transcript into one or more mature rRNA molecules.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgrey
Definition: A cellular process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of a large ribosomal subunit; includes transport to the sites of protein synthesis.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgrey
Definition: A cellular process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of ribosome subunits; includes transport to the sites of protein synthesis.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgrey
Definition: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a nucleosome, the beadlike structural units of eukaryotic chromatin composed of histones and DNA.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgrey
Definition: Recombination occurring within or between DNA molecules in somatic cells.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgrey
Definition: A biological process represents a specific objective that the organism is genetically programmed to achieve. Biological processes are often described by their outcome or ending state, e.g., the biological process of cell division results in the creation of two daughter cells (a divided cell) from a single parent cell. A biological process is accomplished by a particular set of molecular functions carried out by specific gene products (or macromolecular complexes), often in a highly regulated manner and in a particular temporal sequence.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgrey
Definition: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of constituent RNAs and proteins to form the large ribosomal subunit.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgrey
Definition: The directed movement of mRNA, messenger ribonucleic acid, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgrey
term: maturation of SSU-rRNA from tricistronic rRNA transcript (SSU-rRNA, 5.8S rRNA, LSU-rRNA)
Term: maturation of SSU-rRNA from tricistronic rRNA transcript (SSU-rRNA, 5.8S rRNA, LSU-rRNA)
Definition: Any process involved in the maturation of a precursor Small SubUnit (SSU) ribosomal RNA (rRNA) molecule into a mature SSU-rRNA molecule from the pre-rRNA molecule originally produced as a tricistronic rRNA transcript that contains the Small Subunit (SSU) rRNA, 5.8S rRNA, and the Large Subunit (LSU) in that order from 5' to 3' along the primary transcript.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgrey
Definition: The process preceding formation of the peptide bond between the first two amino acids of a protein. This includes the formation of a complex of the ribosome, mRNA or circRNA, and an initiation complex that contains the first aminoacyl-tRNA.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgrey
term: formation of cytoplasmic translation initiation complex
Term: formation of cytoplasmic translation initiation complex
Definition: Joining of the large subunit, with release of IF2/eIF2 and IF3/eIF3. This leaves the functional ribosome at the AUG, with the methionyl/formyl-methionyl-tRNA positioned at the P site.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgrey
Definition: The directed movement of molecules between the nucleus and the cytoplasm.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgrey
Definition: A gene-specific translational control mechanism where the small ribosomal subunit remains attached to the mRNA following termination of translation, then resumes scanning on the same mRNA molecule and initiates again at a downstream start site. Reinitiation depends on de novo recruitment of the ternary complex that is required to recognize the next AUG codon.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgrey
Definition: Any process involved in the maturation of a precursor Large SubUnit (LSU) ribosomal RNA (rRNA) molecule into a mature LSU-rRNA molecule.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgrey
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of RNA, ribonucleic acid, one of the two main type of nucleic acid, consisting of a long, unbranched macromolecule formed from ribonucleotides joined in 3',5'-phosphodiester linkage. Includes polymerization of ribonucleotide monomers. Refers not only to transcription but also to e.g. viral RNA replication.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkgrey
Definition: The directed movement of substances within a cell.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkmagenta
Definition: A cellular process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of inextensible cellulose- and pectin-containing cell walls that are formed between the plasma membrane and primary cell wall after cell expansion is complete. An example of this is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkmagenta
term: regulation of secondary cell wall biogenesis
Term: regulation of secondary cell wall biogenesis
Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of secondary cell wall biogenesis.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkmagenta
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of xylan, a polymer containing a beta-1,4-linked D-xylose backbone.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkmagenta
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of glucuronoxylan, a polymer containing a beta-1,4-linked D-xylose backbone substituted with glucuronic acid residues.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkmagenta
Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cellular DNA-templated transcription.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkmagenta
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of lignins, a class of polymers of phenylpropanoid units.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkmagenta
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of cellulose, a linear beta1-4 glucan of molecular mass 50-400 kDa with the pyranose units in the -4C1 conformation.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkmagenta
Definition: A cellular process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of cellulose and pectin-containing cell walls that form adjacent to the middle lamella following cell division and during cell expansion. An example of this is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkmagenta
Definition: A cellular process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of a cellulose and pectin-containing cell wall. An example of this is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkmagenta
Definition: A type of cell wall modification in which the cell wall is reinforced and made thicker.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkmagenta
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of UDP-D-xylose, uridinediphosphoxylose, a substance composed of xylose in glycosidic linkage with uridine diphosphate.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkmagenta
term: rhamnogalacturonan I side chain metabolic process
Term: rhamnogalacturonan I side chain metabolic process
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways involving the side chains of the pectin, rhamnogalacturonan I.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkmagenta
Definition: NA

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkmagenta
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways involving D-xylose, a naturally occurring plant polysaccharide.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkmagenta
term: plant-type cell wall cellulose biosynthetic process
Term: plant-type cell wall cellulose biosynthetic process
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of cellulose, a linear beta1-4 glucan of molecular mass 50-400 kDa with the pyranose units in the -4C1 conformation, as part of the organization and biogenesis of the cell wall.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkmagenta
term: negative regulation of secondary cell wall biogenesis
Term: negative regulation of secondary cell wall biogenesis
Definition: NA

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkmagenta
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways involving xylan, a polymer containing a beta-(1->4)-linked D-xylose backbone decorated with glucuronic acid side units.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkmagenta
term: positive regulation of syringal lignin biosynthetic process
Term: positive regulation of syringal lignin biosynthetic process
Definition: NA

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkmagenta
Definition: The directed movement of UDP-xylose into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. UDP-xylose is a substance composed of xylose in glycosidic linkage with uridine diphosphate.

name: root.voom5.module.signedhybrid_darkmagenta
Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways involving xylan, a polymer containing a beta-1,4-linked D-xylose backbone.
